properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 5 at 2:39PM PST until January 5 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Storm Warning above 3000 feet, heavy
snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 15 inches. For
the Winter Weather Advisory above 2000 feet, snow continued.
Additional snow accumulations of up to 5 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis
Counties, including the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on
Mount Rainier, White Pass.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from 10 PM this evening
to 10 AM PST Monday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 10
PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING ABOVE 2000 FEET... ...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 AM PST MONDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
